Program 1:To print the given pattern using a for loop in Java:
1. Create a Java class:

    public class PrintPattern {
        public static void main(String[] args) {
            // Loop to print the pattern
            for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
                System.out.println("*");
            }
        }
    }

2. Compile the Java code:
Save the code as PrintPattern.java and compile it using a Java compiler (e.g., javac PrintPattern.java).

3. Run the compiled code:
Execute the compiled class (e.g., java PrintPattern).

This will produce the desired output:
Code

*
*
*
*




Program 2:  You need to develop a simple Java application to print a given pattern using nested loop structures.

Pattern to Print: 
******
******
******
******

program: 

public class patterns {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		int n = 4;
		for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
			System.out.println("*****");
		}

	}

}




Program 3 : You need to develop a simple Java application to print a given pattern using nested loop structures.

Pattern to Print:
1111
2222
3333
4444

Program : 

public class patterns {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		
		for (int i = 1; i <= 4; i++) {
			for (int j = 1; j <= 4; j++) {
				System.out.print(i);
			}
			System.out.println();
		}
		
	}

}





Program 4 : You need to develop a simple Java application to print a given pattern using nested loop structures.

Pattern to Print:

*
**
***
****
*****

Program : 

public class patterns {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		int n = 5;
		for (int i = 0; i <= n; i++) {
			for (int j = 1; j <= i; j++) {
				System.out.print("*");
			}
			System.out.println();
		}
		
	}

}


Program 5 : You need to develop a simple Java application to print a given pattern using nested loop structures.
Pattern :
1
22
333
4444
55555

Program: 
public class patterns {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		
		for (int i = 0; i <= 5; i++) {
			for (int j = 1; j <= i; j++) {
				System.out.print(i);
			}
			System.out.println();
		}
		
	}

}

Program 6 : You need to develop a simple Java application to print a given pattern using nested loop structures.
Pattern :
*****
****
***
**
*

Program :
public class patterns {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		
		for (int i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
			for (int j = 5; j >= i; j--) {
				System.out.print("*");
			}
			System.out.println();
		}
		
	}

}


Program 7 : You need to develop a simple Java application to print a given pattern using nested loop structures.
Pattern :
12345
1234
123
12
1

Program : 
public class patterns {

	public static void main(String[] args) {

		for (int i = 5; i <= 5; i--) {
			for (int j = 1 ; j <= i ; j++) {
			System.out.print(j);
			}
			System.out.println();
			}
		}
		
}


Program 8 : Descending Digits: The Reverse Pyramid
Problem Statement
You need to develop a simple Java application to print a given pattern using nested loop structures.
Pattern to Print:
12345
1234
123
12
1

Program :
public class patterns {

	public static void main(String[] args) {

		for (int i = 5; i <= 5; i--) {
			for (int j = 1 ; j <= i ; j++) {
			System.out.print(j);
			}
			System.out.println();
			}
		}
		
}

Program 9 : Pattern Printing - Vertical Star Line
Question Title:
Pattern Printing - Vertical Line of Stars
Question Description:
Write a Java program to print a vertical line of stars (\*) with exactly one star in each line, up to 5 lines.

Pattern : 
*
*
*
*
*

Program : 
public class VerticalStarLine {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Loop to print 5 stars, each on a new line
        for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
            System.out.println("*"); // Prints a star and moves to the next line
        }
    }
}

Program 10 : You need to develop a simple Java application to print a given pattern
using nested loop structures.

Pattern to Print:
1234
1234
1234

Program :
public class PrintPattern {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++) { // Outer loop for rows
            for (int j = 1; j <= 4; j++) { // Inner loop for printing numbers 1 to 4
                System.out.print(j);
            }
            System.out.println(); // Move to the next line after each row
        }
    }
}
